# Auto Commit and Push

After completing code changes that affect behavior or assets:

- **Commit and push automatically** to **`main`**. Do not ask "should I commit?" or "ready to push?" — just do it.
- **Exception:** If the user explicitly says "don't commit", "don't push", "no deployment", or similar, do not commit or push.

## When to commit and push

- After fixing bugs, adding features, or changing config that should go live.
- After the project builds successfully (fix build/lint errors first if needed).

## When to skip

- User said not to.
- Changes are only temporary, notes, or local-only and the user did not ask to ship them.
